.logo {
  display: inline-flex;
  flex-wrap: nowrap;    /* (3) internal children always one row */
  white-space: nowrap;  /* (2) the link itself is single-line */
  flex-shrink: 0;       /* (1) never yields to siblings */
}

.links {
  min-width: 0; /* absorbs all compression; without this .links can't shrink */
}

.navInner {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: nowrap; /* the outer row never wraps either */
}
```

**See:** FB-146. The original fix attempt applied `flex-shrink: 0` and comments documenting the intent, but omitted `white-space: nowrap` and `flex-wrap: nowrap` on the logo element, leaving the wrap possible under extreme reflow conditions.
